page.title: 06BIRDLIFE AT WEST WITTERING
page.content: East Head at West Wittering is a well known bird watching area.Situated at the head of Chichester harbour,East Head is a favourite place to watch migratory birds in Spring and Autumn. In Spring flocks of swifts,swallows and house martins fly into the area. The cuckoo has been heard.Many finches,warblers and yellowhammers arrive.Avocets have also been noted at East Head. In Autumn the area is well known for the Brent geese which winter in the area.Oyster catchers arrive and other shore birds which include dunlin and lapwings.Field fares and redwing are also winter visitors.The only gulls resident in this area are the black headed gulls,the lesser black_backed gull and the great black_backed gulls. Other gulls are seen in the area occasionally.
